obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (13010)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13010&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be`
  line `called the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India and, save as otherwise provided in this Act, it applies also to`
  line `any offence or contravention thereunder committed outside India by any person.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into fo`
  line `rce on such date`
  line ^1
  line `as the Central Government may, by notificati`
  line `on, appoint and`
  line `different dates may`
  line `be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in any such`
  line `provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the commencement of that`
  line provision.
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4) Nothing in this Act shall apply to documents or transactions specified in the First Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend the First`
  line `Schedule by way of a`
  line ddition
  line `or deletion of entries thereto.`
  line
  line `(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (4) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 17`
  line th
  line `October, 2000,`
  line vide
  line `notification No. G.S.R. 788 (E), dated 17`
  line th
  line `October, 2000,`
  line see
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(`
  line ii
  line `).`
  line
  line 2
  line `Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 3, for sub`
  line -
  line `section (`
  line 4
  line `) (w.e.f. 27`
  line -
  line 10
  line -
  line `2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (13011)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13011&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "access" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions means gaining entry into,`
  line `instructing or communicating with the logical, arithmetical, or memory function resources of a`
  line `computer, computer system or computer network;`
  line
  line `(b) "addressee" means a person who is intended by the originator to receive the electronic record`
  line `but does not include any intermediary;`
  line
  line `(c) "adjudicating officer" means an adjudicating officer appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 46;`
  line
  line `(d) "affixing ^1`
  line `[electronic signature]" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions`
  line `means adoption of any methodology or procedure by a person for the purpose of authenticating an`
  line `electronic record by means of digital signature;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(da) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate Tribunal referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line 48;]
  line
  line `(e) "appropriate Government" means as respects any matter,--`
  line
  line `(i) enumerated in List II of the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(ii) relating to any State law enacted under List III of the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line Constitution,
  line
  line `the State Government and in any other case, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) "asymmetric crypto system" means a system of a secure key pair consisting of a private key`
  line `for creating a digital signature and a public key to verify the digital signature;`
  line
  line `(g) "Certifying Authority" means a person who has been granted a licence to issue a 1`
  line [electronic
  line `signature] Certificate under section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) "certification practice statement" means a statement issued by a Certifying Authority to`
  line `specify the practices that the Certifying Authority employs in issuing ^1`
  line `[electronic signature]`
  line Certificates;
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(ha) "communication device" means cell phones, personal digital assistance or combination of`
  line `both or any other device used to communicate, send or transmit any text, video, audio or image;]`
  line
  line `(i) "computer" means any electronic, magnetic, optical or other high-speed data processing device`
  line `or system which performs logical, arithmetic, and memory functions by manipulations of electronic,`
  line `magnetic or optical impulses, and includes all input, output, processing, storage, computer software or`
  line `communication facilities which are connected or related to the computer in a computer system or`
  line `computer network;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(j) "computer network" means the inter-connection of one or more computers or computer`
  line `systems or communication device through--`
  line
  line `(i) the use of satellite, microwave, terrestrial line, wire, wireless or other communication`
  line `media; and`
  line
  line `(ii) terminals or a complex consisting of two or more interconnected computers or`
  line `communication device whether or not the inter-connection is continuously maintained;]`
  line
  line `(k) "computer resource" means computer, computer system, computer network, data, computer`
  line `data base or software;`
  line
  line `(l) "computer system" means a device or collection of devices, including input and output support`
  line `devices and excluding calculators which are not programmable and capable of being used in`
  line `conjunction with external files, which contain computer programmes, electronic instructions, input`
  line `data and output data, that performs logic, arithmetic, data storage and retrieval, communication`
  line `control and other functions;`
  line
  line `(m) "Controller" means the Controller of Certifying Authorities appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 17;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(na) "cyber cafe" means any facility from where access to the internet is offered by any person`
  line `in the ordinary course of business to the members of the public;`
  line
  line `(nb) "cyber security" means protecting information, equipment, devices, computer, computer`
  line `resource, communication device and information stored therein from unauthorised access, use,`
  line `disclosure, disruption, modification or destruction;]`
  line
  line `(o) "data" means a representation of information, knowledge, facts, concepts or instructions`
  line `which are being prepared or have been prepared in a formalised manner, and is intended to be`
  line `processed, is being processed or has been processed in a computer system or computer network, and`
  line `may be in any form (including computer printouts magnetic or optical storage media, punched cards,`
  line `punched tapes) or stored internally in the memory of the computer;`
  line
  line `(p) "digital signature" means authentication of any electronic record by a subscriber by means of`
  line `an electronic method or procedure in accordance with the provisions of section 3;`
  line
  line `(q) "Digital Signature Certificate" means a Digital Signature Certificate issued under sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(r) "electronic form" with reference to information, means any information generated, sent,`
  line `received or stored in media, magnetic, optical, computer memory, micro film, computer generated`
  line `micro fiche or similar device;`
  line
  line `(s) "Electronic Gazette" means the Official Gazette published in the electronic form;`
  line
  line `(t) "electronic record" means data, record or data generated, image or sound stored, received or`
  line `sent in an electronic form or micro film or computer generated micro fiche;`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(ta) "electronic signature" means authentication of any electronic record by a subscriber by`
  line `means of the electronic technique specified in the Second Schedule and includes digital signature;`
  line
  line `(tb) "Electronic Signature Certificate" means an Electronic Signature Certificate issued under`
  line `section 35 and includes Digital Signature Certificate;]`
  line
  line `(u) "function", in relation to a computer, includes logic, control, arithmetical process, deletion,`
  line `storage and retrieval and communication or telecommunication from or within a computer;`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(ua) Indian Computer Emergency Response Team means an agency established under subsection (1) of Section 70B;]`
  line
  line `(v) "information" includes ^7`
  line `[data, message, text,] images, sound, voice, codes, computer`
  line `programmes, software and data bases or micro film or computer generated micro fiche;`
  line
  line ^8
  line `[(w) "intermediary", with respect to any particular electronic records, means any person who on`
  line `behalf of another person receives, stores or transmits that record or provides any service with respect`
  line `to that record and includes telecom service providers, network service providers, internet service`
  line `providers, web-hosting service providers, search engines, online payment sites, online-auction sites,`
  line `online-market places and cyber cafes;]`
  line
  line `(x) "key pair", in an asymmetric crypto system, means a private key and its mathematically`
  line `related public key, which are so related that the public key can verify a digital signature created by the`
  line `private key;`
  line
  line `(y) "law" includes any Act of Parliament or of a State Legislature, Ordinances promulgated by the`
  line `President or a Governor, as the case may be, Regulations made by the President under article 240,`
  line `Bills enacted as President's Act under sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 357 of the Constitution`
  line `and includes rules, regulations, bye-laws and orders issued or made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(z) "licence" means a licence granted to a Certifying Authority under section 24;`
  line
  line `(za) "originator" means a person who sends, generates, stores or transmits any electronic message`
  line `or causes any electronic message to be sent, generated, stored or transmitted to any other person but`
  line `does not include an intermediary;`
  line
  line `(zb) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(zc) "private key" means the key of a key pair used to create a digital signature;`
  line
  line `(zd) "public key" means the key of a key pair used to verify a digital signature and listed in the`
  line `Digital Signature Certificate;`
  line
  line `(ze) "secure system" means computer hardware, software, and procedure that--`
  line
  line `(a) are reasonably secure from unauthorised access and misuse;`
  line
  line `(b) provide a reasonable level of reliability and correct operation;`
  line
  line `(c) are reasonably suited to performing the intended functions; and`
  line
  line `(d) adhere to generally accepted security procedures;`
  line
  line `(zf) "security procedure" means the security procedure prescribed under section 16 by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(zg) "subscriber" means a person in whose name the ^9`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate is issued;`
  line
  line `(zh) "verify", in relation to a digital signature, electronic record or public key, with its`
  line `grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means to determine whether--`
  line
  line `(a) the initial electronic record was affixed with the digital signature by the use of private key`
  line `corresponding to the public key of the subscriber;`
  line
  line `(b) the initial electronic record is retained intact or has been altered since such electronic`
  line `record was so affixed with the digital signature.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any enactment or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an area in`
  line `which such enactment or such provision is not in force, be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law or the relevant provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "digital signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (j) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Clause (n) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s.169 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 4 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "data, text" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (w) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "digital signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (13012)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Authentication of electronic records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for the heading "DIGITAL SIGNATURE" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13012&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Authentication of electronic records.--(1) Subject to the provisions of this section any subscriber`
  line `may authenticate an electronic record by affixing his digital signature.`
  line
  line `(2) The authentication of the electronic record shall be effected by the use of asymmetric crypto`
  line `system and hash function which envelop and transform the initial electronic record into another electronic`
  line record.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "hash function" means an algorithm mapping or`
  line `translation of one sequence of bits into another, generally smaller, set known as --hash result" such that an`
  line `electronic record yields the same hash result every time the algorithm is executed with the same electronic`
  line `record as its input making it computationally infeasible--`
  line
  line `(a) to derive or reconstruct the original electronic record from the hash result produced by the`
  line algorithm;
  line
  line `(b) that two electronic records can produce the same hash result using the algorithm.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person by the use of a public key of the subscriber can verify the electronic record.`
  line
  line `(4) The private key and the public key are unique to the subscriber and constitute a functioning key`
  line pair.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (13013)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Electronic signature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13013&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[3A. Electronic signature.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 3, but subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), a subscriber may authenticate any electronic record by such electronic`
  line `signature or electronic authentication technique which--`
  line
  line `(a) is considered reliable; and`
  line
  line `(b) may be specified in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section any electronic signature or electronic authentication technique`
  line `shall be considered reliable if--`
  line
  line `(a) the signature creation data or the authentication data are, within the context in which they are`
  line `used, linked to the signatory or, as the case may be, the authenticator and to no other person;`
  line
  line `(b) the signature creation data or the authentication data were, at the time of signing, under the`
  line `control of the signatory or, as the case may be, the authenticator and of no other person;`
  line
  line `(c) any alteration to the electronic signature made after affixing such signature is detectable;`
  line
  line `(d) any alteration to the information made after its authentication by electronic signature is`
  line `detectable; and`
  line
  line `(e) it fulfils such other conditions which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may prescribe the procedure for the purpose of ascertaining whether`
  line `electronic signature is that of the person by whom it is purported to have been affixed or authenticated.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to or omit any`
  line `electronic signature or electronic authentication technique and the procedure for affixing such signature`
  line `from the Second Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that no electronic signature or authentication technique shall be specified in the Second`
  line `Schedule unless such signature or technique is reliable.`
  line
  line `(5) Every notification issued under sub-section (4) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (13014)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Legal recognition of electronic records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13014&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Where any law provides that information or any other`
  line `matter shall be in writing or in the typewritten or printed form, then, notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in such law, such requirement shall be deemed to have been satisfied if such information or matter is--`
  line
  line `(a) rendered or made available in an electronic form; and`
  line
  line `(b) accessible so as to be usable for a subsequent reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (13015)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Legal recognition of electronic signatures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13015&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `5. Legal recognition of ^1`
  line `[electronic signatures].--Where any law provides that information or any`
  line `other matter shall be authenticated by affixing the signature or any document shall be signed or bear the`
  line `signature of any person, then, notwithstanding anything contained in such law, such requirement shall be`
  line `deemed to have been satisfied, if such information or matter is authenticated by means of ^1`
  line [electronic
  line `signature] affixed in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "signed", with its grammatical variations and cognate`
  line `expressions, shall, with reference to a person, mean affixing of his hand written signature or any mark on`
  line `any document and the expression "signature" shall be construed accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "digital signatures"`
  line `(w.e.f. 27`
  line -
  line 10
  line -
  line `2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (13016)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Use of electronic records and electronic signatures in Government and its agencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13016&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `6. Use of electronic records and ^1`
  line `[electronic signatures] in Government and its agencies.--(1)`
  line `Where any law provides for--`
  line
  line `(a) the filing of any form, application or any other document with any office, authority, body or`
  line `agency owned or controlled by the appropriate Government in a particular manner;`
  line
  line `(b) the issue or grant of any licence, permit, sanction or approval by whatever name called in a`
  line `particular manner;`
  line
  line `(c) the receipt or payment of money in a particular manner,`
  line
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, such requirement`
  line `shall be deemed to have been satisfied if such filing, issue, grant, receipt or payment, as the case may be,`
  line `is effected by means of such electronic form as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, for the purposes of sub-section (1), by rules, prescribe--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner and format in which such electronic records shall be filed, created or issued;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner or method of payment of any fee or charges for filing, creation or issue any`
  line `electronic record under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "digital signatures"`
  line `(w.e.f. 27`
  line -
  line 10
  line -
  line `2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (13017)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 8
  title `Delivery of services by service provider.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 7 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13017&sectionno=6A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[6A. Delivery of services by service provider.--(1) The appropriate Government may, for the`
  line `purposes of this Chapter and for efficient delivery of services to the public through electronic means`
  line `authorise, by order, any service provider to set up, maintain and upgrade the computerised facilities and`
  line `perform such other services as it may specify, by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, service provider so authorised includes any`
  line `individual, private agency, private company, partnership firm, sole proprietor firm or any such other body`
  line `or agency which has been granted permission by the appropriate Government to offer services through`
  line `electronic means in accordance with the policy governing such service sector.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may also authorise any service provider authorised under`
  line `sub-section (1) to collect, retain and appropriate such service charges, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government for the purpose of providing such services, from the person availing such`
  line service.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the appropriate Government may authorise the service`
  line `providers to collect, retain and appropriate service charges under this section notwithstanding the fact that`
  line `there is no express provision under the Act, rule, regulation or notification under which the service is`
  line `provided to collect, retain and appropriate e-service charges by the service providers.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the scale of`
  line `service charges which may be charged and collected by the service providers under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government may specify different scale of service charges for different`
  line `types of services.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (13018)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Retention of electronic records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13018&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any law provides that documents, records or`
  line `information shall be retained for any specific period, then, that requirement shall be deemed to have been`
  line `satisfied if such documents, records or information are retained in the electronic form, if--`
  line
  line `(a) the information contained therein remains accessible so as to be usable for a subsequent`
  line reference;
  line
  line `(b) the electronic record is retained in the format in which it was originally generated, sent or`
  line `received or in a format which can be demonstrated to represent accurately the information originally`
  line `generated, sent or received;`
  line
  line `(c) the details which will facilitate the identification of the origin, destination, date and time of`
  line `despatch or receipt of such electronic record are available in the electronic record:`
  line
  line `Provided that this clause does not apply to any information which is automatically generated`
  line `solely for the purpose of enabling an electronic record to be despatched or received.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to any law that expressly provides for the retention of`
  line `documents, records or information in the form of electronic records.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (13019)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 10
  title `Audit of documents, etc., maintained in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13019&sectionno=7A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[7A. Audit of documents, etc., maintained in electronic form.--Where in any law for the time`
  line `being in force, there is a provision for audit of documents, records or information, that provision shall also`
  line `be applicable for audit of documents, records or information processed and maintained in the electronic`
  line form.]
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (13020)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 11
  title `Publication of rule, regulation, etc., in Electronic Gazette.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13020&sectionno=8&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Where any law provides that any`
  line `rule, regulation, order, bye-law, notification or any other matter shall be published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `then, such requirement shall be deemed to have been satisfied if such rule, regulation, order, bye-law,`
  line `notification or any other matter is published in the Official Gazette or Electronic Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any rule, regulation, order, by-law, notification or any other matter is published`
  line `in the Official Gazette or Electronic Gazette, the date of publication shall be deemed to be the date of the`
  line `Gazette which was first published in any form.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (13021)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Sections 6, 7 and 8 not to confer right to insist document should be accepted in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13021&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in sections 6, 7 and 8 shall confer a right upon any person to insist that any`
  line
  line `Ministry or Department of the Central Government or the State Government or any authority or body`
  line es
  line `tablished by or under any law or controlled or funded by the Central or State Government should`
  line `accept, issue, create, retain and preserve any document in the form of electronic records or effect any`
  line `monetary transaction in the electronic form.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (13022)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules by Central Government in respect of electronic signature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "digital signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13022&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. Power to make rules by Central Government in respect of ^1`
  line `[electronic signature].--The`
  line `Central Government may, for the purposes of this Act, by rules, prescribe--`
  line
  line `(a) the type of ^1`
  line `[electronic signature];`
  line
  line `(b) the manner and format in which the ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] shall be affixed;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner or procedure which facilitates identification of the person affixing the ^1`
  line [electronic
  line signature];
  line
  line `(d) control processes and procedures to ensure adequate integrity, security and confidentiality of`
  line `electronic records or payments; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is necessary to give legal effect to ^1`
  line `[electronic signatures].`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (13023)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 14
  title `Validity of contracts formed through electronic means.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13023&sectionno=10A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[10A. Validity of contracts formed through electronic means.--Where in a contract formation,`
  line `the communication of proposals, the acceptance of proposals, the revocation of proposals and`
  line `acceptances, as the case may be, are expressed in electronic form or by means of an electronic records,`
  line `such contract shall not be deemed to be unenforceable solely on the ground that such electronic form or`
  line `means was used for that purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (13024)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 15
  title `Attribution of electronic records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13024&sectionno=11&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `An electronic record shall be attributed to the originator--`
  line
  line `(a) if it was sent by the originator himself;`
  line
  line `(b) by a person who had the authority to act on behalf of the originator in respect of that`
  line `electronic record; or`
  line
  line `(c) by an information system programmed by or on behalf of the originator to operate`
  line automatically
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (13025)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 16
  title `Acknowledgment of receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "agreed with the addressee" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13025&sectionno=12&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the originator has not ^1`
  line `[stipulated] that the`
  line `acknowledgment of receipt of electronic record be given in a particular form or by a particular method, an`
  line `acknowledgment may be given by--`
  line
  line `(a) any communication by the addressee, automated or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(b) any conduct of the addressee, sufficient to indicate to the originator that the electronic record`
  line `has been received.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the originator has stipulated that the electronic record shall be binding only on receipt of an`
  line `acknowledgment of such electronic record by him, then unless acknowledgment has been so received, the`
  line `electronic record shall he deemed to have been never sent by the originator.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the originator has not stipulated that the electronic record shall be binding only on receipt`
  line `of such acknowledgment, and the acknowledgment has not been received by the originator within the`
  line `time specified or agreed or, if no time has been specified or agreed to within a reasonable time, then the`
  line `originator may give notice to the addressee stating that no acknowledgment has been received by him and`
  line `specifying a reasonable time by which the acknowledgment must be received by him and if no`
  line `acknowledgment is received within the aforesaid time limit he may after giving notice to the addressee,`
  line `treat the electronic record as though it has never been sent.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (13026)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 17
  title `Time and place of despatch and receipt of electronic record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13026&sectionno=13&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise agreed to`
  line `between the originator and the addressee, the despatch of an electronic record occurs when it enters a`
  line `computer resource outside the control of the originator.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise agreed between the originator and the addressee, the time of receipt of an`
  line `electronic record shall be determined as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the addressee has designated a computer resource for the purpose of receiving electronic`
  line records,--
  line
  line `(i) receipt occurs at the time when the electronic record enters the designated computer`
  line `resource; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the electronic record is sent to a computer resource of the addressee that is not the`
  line `designated computer resource, receipt occurs at the time when the electronic record is retrieved`
  line `by the addressee;`
  line
  line `(b) if the addressee has not designated a computer resource along with specified timings, if any,`
  line `receipt occurs when the electronic record enters the computer resource of the addressee.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise agreed to between the originator and the addressee, an electronic record is`
  line `deemed to be despatched at the place where the originator has his place of business, and is deemed to be`
  line `received at the place where the addressee has his place of business.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply notwithstanding that the place where the computer`
  line `resource is located may be different from the place where the electronic record is deemed to have been`
  line `received under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the originator or the addressee has more than one place of business, the principal place of`
  line `business, shall be the place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) if the originator or the addressee does not have a place of business, his usual place of`
  line `residence shall be deemed to be the place of business;`
  line
  line `(c) "usual place of residence", in relation to a body corporate, means the place where it is`
  line registered.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (13027)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 18
  title `Secure electronic record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13027&sectionno=14&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where any security procedure has been applied to an electronic`
  line `record at a specific point of time, then such record shall he deemed to be a secure electronic record from`
  line `such point of time to the time of verification.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (13028)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Secure electronic signature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by s 11, ibid., for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13028&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[15. Secure electronic signature.--An electronic signature shall be deemed to be a secure electronic`
  line `signature if--`
  line
  line `(i) the signature creation data, at the time of affixing signature, was under the exclusive control of`
  line `signatory and no other person; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the signature creation data was stored and affixed in such exclusive manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In case of digital signature, the "signature creation data" means the private key of the`
  line subscriber.]
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (13029)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 20
  title `Security procedures and practices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s 11, ibid., for sections 15 and 16 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13029&sectionno=16&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Security procedures and practices.--The Central Government may, for the purposes of sections`
  line `14 and 15, prescribe the security procedures and practices:`
  line
  line `Provided that in prescribing such security procedures and practices, the Central Government shall`
  line `have regard to the commercial circumstances, nature of transactions and such other related factors as it`
  line `may consider appropriate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (13030)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 21
  title `Appointment of Controller and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13030&sectionno=17&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a Controller of Certifying Authorities for the purposes of this`
  line `Act and may also by the same or subsequent notification appoint such number of Deputy Controllers`
  line ^1
  line `[, Assistant Controllers, other officers and employees] as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall discharge his functions under this Act subject to the general control and`
  line `directions of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Deputy Controllers and Assistant Controllers shall perform the functions assigned to them by`
  line `the Controller under the general superintendence and control of the Controller.`
  line
  line `(4) The qualifications, experience and terms and conditions of service of Controller, Deputy`
  line `Controllers ^2`
  line `[,Assistant Controllers, other officers and employees] shall be such as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Head Office and Branch Office of the office of the Controller shall be at such places as the`
  line `Central Government may specify, and these may be established at such places as the Central Government`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `(6) There shall be a seal of the Office of the Controller.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by s.12, ibid., for "and Assistant Controllers" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 12, for "Assistant Controllers" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (13031)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 22
  title `Functions of Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13031&sectionno=18&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Controller may perform all or any of the following functions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) exercising supervision over the activities of the Certifying Authorities;`
  line
  line `(b) certifying public keys of the Certifying Authorities;`
  line
  line `(c) laying down the standards to be maintained by the Certifying Authorities;`
  line
  line `(d) specifying the qualifications and experience which employees of the Certifying Authority`
  line `should possess;`
  line
  line `(e) specifying the conditions subject to which the Certifying Authorities shall conduct their`
  line business;
  line
  line `(f) specifying the contents of written, printed or visual materials and advertisements that may be`
  line `distributed or used in respect of a ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate and the public key;`
  line
  line `(g) specifying the form and content of a ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate and the key;`
  line
  line `(h) specifying the form and manner in which accounts shall be maintained by the Certifying`
  line Authorities;
  line
  line `(i) specifying the terms and conditions subject to which auditors may be appointed and the`
  line `remuneration to be paid to them;`
  line
  line `(j) facilitating the establishment of any electronic system by a Certifying Authority either solely`
  line `or jointly with other Certifying Authorities and regulation of such systems;`
  line
  line `(k) specifying the manner in which the Certifying Authorities shall conduct their dealings with the`
  line subscribers;
  line
  line `(l) resolving any conflict of interests between the Certifying Authorities and the subscribers;`
  line
  line `(m) laying down the duties of the Certifying Authorities;`
  line
  line `(n) maintaining a data base containing the disclosure record of every Certifying Authority`
  line `containing such particulars as may be specified by regulations, which shall be accessible to public.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (13032)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 23
  title `Recognition of foreign Certifying Authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13032&sectionno=19&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions and restrictions`
  line `as may be specified by regulations, the Controller may with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, and by notification in the Official Gazette, recognise any foreign Certifying Authority as a`
  line `Certifying Authority for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any Certifying Authority is recognised under sub-section (1), the ^1`
  line `[electronic signature]`
  line `Certificate issued by such Certifying Authority shall be valid for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller may, if he is satisfied that any Certifying Authority has contravened any of the`
  line `conditions and restrictions subject to which it was granted recognition under sub-section (1) he may, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, by notification in the Official Gazette, revoke such recognition.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (13033)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13033&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `20. [Controller to act as repository.]Omitted by the Information Technology (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2008 (10 of 2009), s. 13 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (13034)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Licence to issue electronic signature Certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13034&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `21. Licence to issue ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificates.--(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), any person may make an application, to the Controller, for a licence to issue ^1`
  line [electronic
  line `signature] Certificates.`
  line
  line `(2) No licence shall be issued under sub-section (1), unless the applicant fulfils such requirements`
  line `with respect to qualification, expertise, manpower, financial resources and other infrastructure facilities,`
  line `which are necessary to issue ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificates as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) A licence granted under this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be valid for such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) not be transferable or heritable;`
  line
  line `(c) be subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (13035)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Application for licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13035&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every application for issue of a licence shall be in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for issue of a licence shall be accompanied by--`
  line
  line `(a) a certification practice statement;`
  line
  line `(b) a statement including the procedures with respect to identification of the applicant;`
  line
  line `(c) payment of such fees, not exceeding twenty-five thousand rupees as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) such other documents, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (13036)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Renewal of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13036&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `An application for renewal of a licence shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) in such form;`
  line
  line `(b) accompanied by such fees, not exceeding five thousand rupees, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government and shall be made not less than forty-five days before the date of expiry of the`
  line `period of validity of the licence.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (13037)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure for grant or rejection of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13037&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Controller may, on receipt of an application`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 21, after considering the documents accompanying the application and`
  line `such other factors, as he deems fit, grant the licence or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected under this section unless the applicant has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of presenting his case.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (13038)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 29
  title `Suspension of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13038&sectionno=25&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller may, if he is satisfied after making such inquiry, as`
  line `he may think fit, that a Certifying Authority has--`
  line
  line `(a) made a statement in, or in relation to, the application for the issue or renewal of the licence,`
  line `which is incorrect or false in material particulars;`
  line
  line `(b) failed to comply with the terms and conditions subject to which the licence was granted;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) failed to maintain the procedures and standards specified in section 30;]`
  line
  line `(d) contravened any provisions of this Act, rule, regulation or order made thereunder,`
  line
  line `revoke the licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence shall be revoked unless the Certifying Authority has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the proposed revocation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller may, if he has reasonable cause to believe that there is any ground for revoking a`
  line `licence under sub-section (1), by order suspend such licence pending the completion of any enquiry`
  line `ordered by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence shall be suspended for a period exceeding ten days unless the Certifying`
  line `Authority has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed suspension.`
  line
  line `(3) No Certifying Authority whose licence has been suspended shall issue any ^2`
  line `[electronic signature]`
  line `Certificate during such suspension`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by notification No. S.O. 1015(E) (w.e.f. 19-9-2002)`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (13039)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 30
  title `Notice of suspension or revocation of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13039&sectionno=26&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the licence of the Certifying`
  line `Authority is suspended or revoked, the Controller shall publish notice of such suspension or revocation,`
  line `as the case may be, in the data base maintained by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Where one or more repositories are specified, the Controller shall publish notices of such`
  line `suspension or revocation, as the case may be, in all such repositories:`
  line
  line `Provided that the data base containing the notice of such suspension or revocation, as the case may`
  line `be, shall be made available through a web site which shall be accessible round the clock:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Controller may, if he considers necessary, publicise the contents of data base`
  line `in such electronic or other media, as he may consider appropriate.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (13040)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13040&sectionno=27&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Controller may, in writing, authorise the Deputy Controller, Assistant`
  line `Controller or any officer to exercise any of the powers of the Controller under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (13041)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to investigate contraventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13041&sectionno=28&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller or any officer authorised by him in`
  line `this behalf shall take up for investigation any contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller or any officer authorised by him in this behalf shall exercise the like powers which`
  line `are conferred on Income-tax authorities under Chapter XIII of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), and`
  line `shall exercise such powers, subject to such limitations laid down under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (13042)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 33
  title `Access to computers and data.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13042&sectionno=29&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 69, the Controller or any person authorised by him shall, if he has reasonable cause to suspect that`
  line ^1
  line `[any contravention of the provisions of this Chapter] has been committed, have access to any computer`
  line `system, any apparatus, data or any other material connected with such system, for the purpose of`
  line `searching or causing a search to be made for obtaining any information or data contained in or available`
  line `to such computer system.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Controller or any person authorised by him may, by order,`
  line `direct any person in charge of, or otherwise concerned with the operation of, the computer system, data`
  line `apparatus or material, to provide him with such reasonable technical and other assistance as he may`
  line `consider necessary`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "any contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules and regulations made thereunder"`
  line `(w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (13043)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 34
  title `Certifying Authority to follow certain procedures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13043&sectionno=30&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Every Certifying Authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) make use of hardware, software and procedures that are secure from intrusion and misuse;`
  line
  line `(b) provide a reasonable level of reliability in its services which are reasonably suited to the`
  line `performance of intended functions;`
  line
  line `(c) adhere to security procedures to ensure that the secrecy and privacy of the ^1`
  line [electronic
  line `signatures] are assured; ^2`
  line ***
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(ca) be the repository of all electronic signature Certificates issued under this Act;`
  line
  line `(cb) publish information regarding its practices, electronic signature Certificates and current`
  line `status of such certificates; and]`
  line
  line `(d) observe such other standards as may be specified by regulations`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (13044)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 35
  title `Certifying Authority to ensure compliance of the Act, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13044&sectionno=31&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every Certifying Authority shall`
  line `ensure that every person employed or otherwise engaged by it complies, in the course of his employment`
  line `or engagement, with the provisions of this Act, rules, regulations and orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (13045)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 36
  title `Display of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13045&sectionno=32&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every Certifying Authority shall display its licence at a conspicuous place`
  line `of the premises in which it carries on its business.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (13046)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 37
  title `Surrender of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13046&sectionno=33&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Certifying Authority whose licence is suspended or revoked`
  line `shall immediately after such suspension or revocation, surrender the licence to the Controller.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any Certifying Authority fails to surrender a licence under sub-section (1), the person in`
  line `whose favour a licence is issued, shall be guilty of an offence and shall be ^1]liable to penalty which may`
  line `extend to five lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (13047)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 38
  title Disclosure.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13047&sectionno=34&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Certifying Authority shall disclose in the manner specified by`
  line regulations--
  line
  line `(a) its ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate ^2`
  line ***;
  line
  line `(b) any certification practice statement relevant thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) notice of the revocation or suspension of its Certifying Authority certificate, if any; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other fact that materially and adversely affects either the reliability of a ^1`
  line `[electronic signature]`
  line `Certificate, which that Authority has issued, or the Authority's ability to perform its services.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in the opinion of the Certifying Authority any event has occurred or any situation has`
  line `arisen which may materially and adversely affect the integrity of its computer system or the conditions`
  line `subject to which a ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate was granted, then, the Certifying Authority shall--`
  line
  line `(a) use reasonable efforts to notify any person who is likely to be affected by that occurrence; or`
  line
  line `(b) act in accordance with the procedure specified in its certification practice statement to deal`
  line `with such event or situation.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (13048)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 39
  title `Certifying authority to issue electronic signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13048&sectionno=35&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `35. Certifying authority to issue ^1[electronic signature] Certificate.--(1) Any person may make an`
  line `application to the Certifying Authority for the issue of a ^1[electronic signature] Certificate in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such application shall be accompanied by such fee not exceeding twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees as may be prescribed by the Central Government, to be paid to the Certifying Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that while prescribing fees under sub-section (2) different fees may be prescribed for`
  line `different classes of applicants.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such application shall be accompanied by a certification practice statement or where there is`
  line `no such statement, a statement containing such particulars, as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Certifying Authority may, after`
  line `consideration of the certification practice statement or the other statement under sub-section (3) and after`
  line `making such enquiries as it may deem fit, grant the ^1[electronic signature] Certificate or for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, reject the application:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[Provided] that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the proposed rejection.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. The first proviso omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "Provided further" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (13049)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 40
  title `Representations upon issuance of Digital signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 18 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13049&sectionno=36&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `A Certifying Authority`
  line `while issuing a Digital Signature Certificate shall certify that--`
  line
  line `(a) it has complied with the provisions of this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) it has published the Digital Signature Certificate or otherwise made it available to such person`
  line `relying on it and the subscriber has accepted it;`
  line
  line `(c) the subscriber holds the private key corresponding to the public key, listed in the Digital`
  line `Signature Certificate;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ca) the subscriber holds a private key which is capable of creating a digital signature;`
  line
  line `(cb) the public key to be listed in the certificate can be used to verify a digital signature affixed by`
  line `the private key held by the subscriber;]`
  line
  line `(d) the subscriber's public key and private key constitute a functioning key pair;`
  line
  line `(e) the information contained in the Digital Signature Certificate is accurate; and`
  line
  line `(f) it has no knowledge of any material fact, which if it had been included in the Digital Signature Certificate would adversely affect the reliability of the representations in clauses (a) to (d).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (13050)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 41
  title `Suspension of Digital Signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13050&sectionno=37&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the`
  line `Certifying Authority which has issued a Digital Signature Certificate may suspend such Digital Signature`
  line Certificate,–
  line `(a) on receipt of a request to that effect from–`
  line `(i) the subscriber listed in the Digital Signature Certificate; or`
  line `(ii) any person duly authorised to act on behalf of that subscriber;`
  line `(b) if it is of opinion that the Digital Signature Certificate should be suspended in public interest.`
  line `(2) A Digital Signature Certificate shall not be suspended for a period exceeding fifteen days unless`
  line `the subscriber has been given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line `(3) On suspension of a Digital Signature Certificate under this section, the Certifying Authority shall`
  line `communicate the same to the subscriber.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (13051)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 42
  title `Revocation of Digital Signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13051&sectionno=38&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Certifying Authority may revoke a Digital`
  line `Signature Certificate issued by it--`
  line
  line `(a) where the subscriber or any other person authorised by him makes a request to that effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) upon the death of the subscriber; or`
  line
  line `(c) upon the dissolution of the firm or winding up of the company where the subscriber is a firm`
  line `or a company.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) and without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), a Certifying Authority may revoke a Digital Signature Certificate which has been issued`
  line `by it at any time, if it is of opinion that--`
  line
  line `(a) a material fact represented in the Digital Signature Certificate is false or has been concealed;`
  line
  line `(b) a requirement for issuance of the Digital Signature Certificate was not satisfied;`
  line
  line `(c) the Certifying Authority's private key or security system was compromised in a manner`
  line `materially affecting the Digital Signature Certificate's reliability;`
  line
  line `(d) the subscriber has been declared insolvent or dead or where a subscriber is a firm or a`
  line `company, which has been dissolved, wound-up or otherwise ceased to exist.`
  line
  line `(3) A Digital Signature Certificate shall not be revoked unless the subscriber has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) On revocation of a Digital Signature Certificate under this section, the Certifying Authority shall`
  line `communicate the same to the subscriber.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (13052)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 43
  title `Notice of suspension or revocation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13052&sectionno=39&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Digital Signature Certificate is suspended or`
  line `revoked under section 37 or section 38, the Certifying Authority shall publish a notice of such suspension`
  line `or revocation, as the case may be, in the repository specified in the Digital Signature Certificate for`
  line `publication of such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Where one or more repositories are specified, the Certifying Authority shall publish notices of`
  line `such suspension or revocation, as the case may be, in all such repositories.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (13053)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 44
  title `Generating key pair.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13053&sectionno=40&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where any Digital Signature Certificate the public key of which`
  line `corresponds to the private key of that subscriber which is to be listed in the Digital Signature Certificate`
  line `has been accepted by a subscriber, ^1`
  line `*** the subscriber shall generate ^2`
  line `[that key] pair by applying the`
  line `security procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "then" omitted by notification No. S.O. 1015(E) (w.e.f. 19-9-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. ibid., for "the key" (w.e.f. 19-9-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (13054)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 45
  title `Duties of subscriber of Electronic Signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
  footnotes `1Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 19 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13054&sectionno=40A&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[40A. Duties of subscriber of Electronic Signature Certificate.--In respect of Electronic Signature`
  line `Certificate the subscriber shall perform such duties as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (13055)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 46
  title `Acceptance of Digital Signature Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13055&sectionno=41&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) A subscriber shall be deemed to have accepted`
  line `a Digital Signature Certificate if he publishes or authorises the publication of a Digital Signature`
  line Certificate--
  line
  line `(a) to one or more persons;`
  line
  line `(b) in a repository; or`
  line
  line `otherwise demonstrates his approval of the Digital Signature Certificate in any manner.`
  line
  line `(2) By accepting a Digital Signature Certificate the subscriber certifies to all who reasonably rely on`
  line `the information contained in the Digital Signature Certificate that--`
  line
  line `(a) the subscriber holds the private key corresponding to the public key listed in the Digital`
  line `Signature Certificate and is entitled to hold the same;`
  line
  line `(b) all representations made by the subscriber to the Certifying Authority and all material relevant`
  line `to the information contained in the Digital Signature Certificate are true;`
  line
  line `(c) all information in the Digital Signature Certificate that is within the knowledge of the`
  line `subscriber is true.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (13056)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 47
  title `Control of private key.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13056&sectionno=42&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every subscriber shall exercise reasonable care to retain control of`
  line `the private key corresponding to the public key listed in his Digital Signature Certificate and take all steps`
  line `to prevent its disclosure ^1`
  line ***
  line
  line `(2) If the private key corresponding to the public key listed in the Digital Signature Certificate has`
  line `been compromised, then, the subscriber shall communicate the same without any delay to the Certifying`
  line `Authority in such manner as may be specified by the regulations.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the subscriber shall be liable till he`
  line `has informed the Certifying Authority that the private key has been compromised.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "to a person not authorised to affix the digital signature of the subscriber" omitted by notification No. S.O.1015(E)`
  line `(w.e.f. 19-9-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (13057)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty and compensation for damage to computer, computer system, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13057&sectionno=43&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line ^1[43.
  line ^2
  line `[Penalty and compensation] for damage to computer, computer system, etc.--If any person`
  line `without permission of the owner or any other person who is in charge of a computer, computer system or`
  line `computer network,--`
  line
  line `(a) accesses or secures access to such computer, computer system or computer network`
  line ^3
  line `[or computer resource];`
  line
  line `(b) downloads, copies or extracts any data, computer data base or information from such`
  line `computer, computer system or computer network including information or data held or stored in any`
  line `removable storage medium;`
  line
  line `(c) introduces or causes to be introduced any computer contaminant or computer virus into any`
  line `computer, computer system or computer network;`
  line
  line `(d) damages or causes to be damaged any computer, computer system or computer network, data,`
  line `computer data base or any other programmes residing in such computer, computer system or`
  line `computer network;`
  line
  line `(e) disrupts or causes disruption of any computer, computer system or computer network;`
  line
  line `(f) denies or causes the denial of access to any person authorised to access any computer,`
  line `computer system or computer network by any means;`
  line
  line `(g) provides any assistance to any person to facilitate access to a computer, computer system or`
  line `computer network in contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules or regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(h) charges the services availed of by a person to the account of another person by tampering with`
  line `or manipulating any computer, computer system, or computer network;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(i) destroys, deletes or alters any information residing in a computer resource or diminishes its`
  line `value or utility or affects it injuriously by any means;`
  line
  line `(j) steal, conceal, destroys or alters or causes any person to steal, conceal, destroy or alter any`
  line `computer source code used for a computer resource with an intention to cause damage;]`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[he shall be liable to pay damages by way of compensation to the person so affected.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "computer contaminant" means any set of computer instructions that are designed--`
  line
  line `(a) to modify, destroy, record, transmit data or programme residing within a computer,`
  line `computer system or computer network; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any means to usurp the normal operation of the computer, computer system, or`
  line `computer network;`
  line
  line `(ii) "computer data-base" means a representation of information, knowledge, facts, concepts or`
  line `instructions in text, image, audio, video that are being prepared or have been prepared in a formalised`
  line `manner or have been produced by a computer, computer system or computer network and are`
  line `intended for use in a computer, computer system or computer network;`
  line
  line `(iii) "computer virus" means any computer instruction, information, data or programme that`
  line `destroys, damages, degrades or adversely affects the performance of a computer resource or attaches`
  line `itself to another computer resource and operates when a programme, data or instruction is executed or`
  line `some other event takes place in that computer resource;`
  line
  line `(iv) "damage" means to destroy, alter, delete, add, modify or rearrange any computer resource by`
  line `any means.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(v) "computer source code" means the listing of programme, computer commands, design and`
  line `layout and programme analysis of computer resource in any form.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 20, for "PENALTIES AND ADJUDICATION" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "Penalty" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 21 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `5Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (13058)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 49
  title `Compensation for failure to protect data.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13058&sectionno=43A&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[43A. Compensation for failure to protect data.--Where a body corporate, possessing, dealing or`
  line `handling any sensitive personal data or information in a computer resource which it owns, controls or`
  line `operates, is negligent in implementing and maintaining reasonable security practices and procedures and`
  line `thereby causes wrongful loss or wrongful gain to any person, such body corporate shall be liable to pay`
  line `damages by way of compensation to the person so affected.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "body corporate" means any company and includes a firm, sole proprietorship or other`
  line `association of individuals engaged in commercial or professional activities;`
  line
  line `(ii) "reasonable security practices and procedures" means security practices and procedures`
  line `designed to protect such information from unauthorised access, damage, use, modification, disclosure`
  line `or impairment, as may be specified in an agreement between the parties or as may be specified in any`
  line `law for the time being in force and in the absence of such agreement or any law, such reasonable`
  line `security practices and procedures, as may be prescribed by the Central Government in consultation`
  line `with such professional bodies or associations as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(iii) "sensitive personal data or information" means such personal information as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with such professional bodies or associations as`
  line `it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (13059)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 50
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information, return, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13059&sectionno=44&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If any person who is required under this`
  line `Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder to--`
  line
  line `(a) furnish any document, return or report to the Controller or the Certifying Authority fails to`
  line `furnish the same, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding ^1[fifteen lakh] rupees for each such`
  line failure;
  line
  line `(b) file any return or furnish any information, books or other documents within the time specified`
  line `therefor in the regulations fails to file return or furnish the same within the time specified therefor in`
  line `the regulations, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding ^2[fifty thousand] rupees for every day`
  line `during which such failure continues;`
  line
  line `(c) maintain books of account or records, fails to maintain the same, he shall be liable to a penalty`
  line `not exceeding ^3[one lakh] rupees for every day during which the failure continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for "one lakh and fifty thousand" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid., s. 2 and Schedule, for "five thousand" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (13060)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 51
  title `Residuary penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13060&sectionno=45&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any ^1[rules, regulations, directions or orders] made`
  line `under this Act, for the contravention of which no penalty has been separately provided, shall be liable to`
  line `pay a ^2[penalty not exceeding one lakh rupees, in addition to compensation to the person affected by such`
  line `contravention not exceeding--`
  line `(a) ten lakh rupees, by an intermediary, company or body corporate; or/be`
  line `(b) one lakh rupees, by any other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by ibid., s. 2 and Schedule, for "rules or regulations" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by ibid., s. 2 and Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (13061)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13061&sectionno=46&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging ^1[under this Act] whether any person has`
  line `committed a contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule, regulation, ^2[direction or`
  line `order made thereunder which renders him liable to pay penalty or compensation,] the Central Government`
  line `shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), appoint any officer not below the rank of a Director to`
  line `the Government of India or an equivalent officer of a State Government to be an adjudicating officer for`
  line `holding an inquiry in the manner prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) The adjudicating officer appointed under sub-section (1) shall exercise jurisdiction to`
  line `adjudicate matters in which the claim for ^4*** damage does not exceed rupees five crore:`
  line `Provided that the jurisdiction in respect of the claim for ^4*** damage exceeding rupees five crores`
  line `shall vest with the competent court.]`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer shall, after giving the person referred to in sub-section (1) a reasonable`
  line `opportunity for making representation in the matter and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has committed the contravention, he may impose such penalty or award such compensation as he thinks`
  line `fit in accordance with the provisions of that section.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be appointed as an adjudicating officer unless he possesses such experience in the`
  line `field of Information Technology and legal or judicial experience as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) Where more than one adjudicating officers are appointed, the Central Government shall specify by`
  line `order the matters and places with respect to which such officers shall exercise their jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(5) Every adjudicating officer shall have the powers of a civil court which are conferred on the`
  line `^5[Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (2) of section 58, and--`
  line
  line `(a) all proceedings before it shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of`
  line `sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of sections 345 and 346 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `^6[(c) shall be deemed to be a civil court for purposes of Order XXI of the Civil Procedure Code,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908).]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by ibid., s. 2 and Schedule, for "under this Chapter" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 23, for "direction or order made thereunder" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Words omitted "injury or" omitted by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 23 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (13062)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 53
  title `Factors to be taken into account by the adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13062&sectionno=47&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `While adjudging the quantum of`
  line `compensation under this Chapter, the adjudicating officer shall have due regard to the following factors,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of gain of unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of loss caused to any person as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the default.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (13063)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 54
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13063&sectionno=48&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `48.^2[Appellate Tribunal].--`
  line `^3[(1) The Telecom Disputes Settlement and Appellate Tribunal`
  line `established under section 14 of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997), shall,`
  line `on and from the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), be the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal for the purposes of this Act and the said Appellate Tribunal shall exercise the`
  line `jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government ^4[shall specify, by notification] the matters and places in relation to`
  line `which the ^1[Appellate Tribunal] may exercise jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 169, ibid., for " Establishment of Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 169, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 169, ibid., for "shall also specify, in the notification referred to in sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
