obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (13076)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 67
  title `Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s, 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13076&sectionno=57&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `57. Appeal to ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal].--(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2), any person aggrieved`
  line `by an order made by controller or an adjudicating officer under this Act may prefer an appeal to a`
  line ^1
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie to the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] from an order made by an adjudicating officer`
  line `with the consent of the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order made by the Controller or the adjudicating officer is received by the person`
  line `aggrieved and it shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] may, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The ^1`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal`
  line `and to the concerned Controller or adjudicating officer.`
  line
  line `(6) The appeal filed before the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within six`
  line `months from the date of receipt of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (13077)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 68
  title `Procedure and powers of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s, 169, for 'Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13077&sectionno=58&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] shall not be`
  line `bound by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided`
  line `by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and of any rules, the`
  line ^1
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] shall have powers to regulate its own procedure including the place at which it shall`
  line `have its sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act,`
  line `the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents or other electronic records;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding before the`
  line `^1[Appellate Tribunal] shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding`
  line `within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) and the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section`
  line `195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (13078)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 69
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s, 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13078&sectionno=59&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The appellant may either appear in person or authorise one or`
  line `more legal practitioners or any of its officers to present his or its case before the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal].`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (13079)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 70
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s, 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13079&sectionno=60&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to an appeal made to the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal].`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (13080)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 71
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169, for 'Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13080&sectionno=61&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `No court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or`
  line `proceeding in respect of any matter which an adjudicating officer appointed under this Act or the`
  line ^1
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] constituted under this Act is empowered by or under this Act to determine and no`
  line `injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in`
  line `pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (13081)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 72
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13081&sectionno=62&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the ^60`
  line Appellate
  line `Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court within sixty days from the date of communication of the`
  line `decision or order of the ^1`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] to him on any question of fact or law arising out of such`
  line `order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (13082)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 73
  title `Compounding of contraventions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by notification No. S.O. 1015(E) (w.e.f. 19-9-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13082&sectionno=63&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any contravention under this ^1`
  line `[Act] may, either before or`
  line `after the institution of adjudication proceedings, be compounded by the Controller or such other officer as`
  line `may be specially authorised by him in this behalf or by the adjudicating officer, as the case may be,`
  line `subject to such conditions as the Controller or such other officer or the adjudicating officer may specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the penalty which may`
  line `be imposed under this Act for the contravention so compounded.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to a person who commits the same or similar contravention`
  line `within a period of three years from the date on which the first contravention, committed by him, was`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, any second or subsequent contravention`
  line `committed after the expiry of a period of three years from the date on which the contravention was`
  line `previously compounded shall be deemed to be a first contravention.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any contravention has been compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further`
  line `proceeding, as the case may be, shall be taken against the person guilty of such contravention in respect of`
  line `the contravention so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (13083)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 74
  title `Recovery of penalty or compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13083&sectionno=64&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `64. Recovery of ^1`
  line `[penalty or compensation].--A ^2`
  line `[penalty imposed or compensation awarded] under`
  line `this Act, if it is not paid, shall he recovered as an arrear of land revenue and the licence or the ^3`
  line [electronic
  line `signature] Certificate, as the case may be, shall be suspended till the penalty is paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line `1Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 31, for "penalty" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "penalty imposed" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (13084)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 75
  title `Tampering with computer source documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13084&sectionno=65&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly or intentionally conceals,`
  line `destroys or alters or intentionally or knowingly causes another to conceal, destroy, or alter any computer`
  line `source code used for a computer, computer programme, computer system or computer network, when the`
  line `computer source code is required to be kept or maintained by law for the time being in force, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment up to three years, or with fine which may extend up to two lakh rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, 'computer source code" means the listing of`
  line `programmes, computer commands, design and layout and programme analysis of computer resource in`
  line `any form`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (13085)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 76
  title `Computer related offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sections 66 and 67 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13085&sectionno=66&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[66. Computer related offences.-- If any person, dishonestly or fraudulently, does any act referred to`
  line `in section 43, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or`
  line `with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the word "dishonestly" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 24 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(b) the word "fraudulently" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 25 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_66_a:
  sectionId (13086)
  sectionNo 66A
  orderNo 77
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13086&sectionno=66A&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[66A. Punishment for sending offensive messages through communication service, etc.--Any`
  line `person who sends, by means of a computer resource or a communication device,`
  line
  line `(a) any information that is grossly offensive or has menacing character; or`
  line
  line `(b) any information which he knows to be false, but for the purpose of causing annoyance,`
  line `inconvenience, danger, obstruction, insult, injury, criminal intimidation, enmity, hatred or ill will,`
  line `persistently by making use of such computer resource or a communication device;`
  line
  line `(c) any electronic mail or electronic mail message for the purpose of causing annoyance or`
  line `inconvenience or to deceive or to mislead the addressee or recipient about the origin of such`
  line messages,
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, terms "electronic mail" and "electronic mail message"`
  line `means a message or information created or transmitted or received on a computer, computer system,`
  line `computer resource or communication device including attachments in text, image, audio, video and any`
  line `other electronic record, which may be transmitted with the message.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 66A has been struck down by Supreme Court's Order dated 24th March, 2015 in the Shreya Singhal vs. Union of India,`
  line `AIR 2015 SC. 1523.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_b:
  sectionId (13087)
  sectionNo 66B
  orderNo 78
  title `Punishment for dishonestly receiving stolen computer resource or communication device.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13087&sectionno=66B&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_b_content:
  string
  line `Whoever dishonestly receive or retains any stolen computer resource or communication device`
  line `knowing or having reason to believe the same to be stolen computer resource or communication device,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years or`
  line `with fine which may extend to rupees one lakh or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66_c:
  sectionId (13088)
  sectionNo 66C
  orderNo 79
  title `Punishment for identity theft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13088&sectionno=66C&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_c_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, fraudulently or dishonestly make use of the`
  line `electronic signature, password or any other unique identification feature of any other person, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine which may extend to rupees one lakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66_d:
  sectionId (13089)
  sectionNo 66D
  orderNo 80
  title `Punishment for cheating by personation by using computer resource.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13089&sectionno=66D&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_d_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, by means of`
  line `any communication device or computer resource cheats by personation, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years and shall also be liable to`
  line `fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_d_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66_e:
  sectionId (13090)
  sectionNo 66E
  orderNo 81
  title `Punishment for violation of privacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_e_content
  footnotes `*. By Corrigenda in Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, Section I, dated 5-2-2009.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13090&sectionno=66E&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_e_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, intentionally or knowingly captures, publishes`
  line `or transmits the image of a private area of any person without his or her consent, under circumstances`
  line `violating the privacy of that person, shall be punished with imprisonment which may extend to three years`
  line `or with fine not exceeding two lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) transmit means to electronically send a visual image with the intent that it be viewed by a`
  line `person or persons;`
  line
  line `(b) capture, with respect to an image, means to videotape, photograph, film or record by any`
  line means;
  line
  line `(c) private area means the naked or undergarment clad genitals, *[pubic area], buttocks or female`
  line `breast:`
  line
  line `(d) publishes means reproduction in the printed or electronic form and making it available for`
  line public;
  line
  line `(e) under circumstances violating privacy means circumstances in which a person can have a`
  line `reasonable expectation that--`
  line
  line `(i) he or she could disrobe in privacy, without being concerned that an image of his private`
  line `area was being captured; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any part of his or her private area would not be visible to the public, regardless of whether`
  line `that person is in a public or private place.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_f:
  sectionId (13091)
  sectionNo 66F
  orderNo 82
  title `Punishment for cyber terrorism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13091&sectionno=66F&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_66_f_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(A) with intent to threaten the unity, integrity, security or sovereignty of India or to strike terror in`
  line `the people or any section of the people by--`
  line
  line `(i) denying or cause the denial of access to any person authorised to access computer`
  line `resource; or`
  line
  line `(ii) attempting to penetrate or access a computer resource without authorisation or exceeding`
  line `authorised access; or`
  line
  line `(iii) introducing or causing to introduce any computer contaminant,`
  line
  line `and by means of such conduct causes or is likely to cause death or injuries to persons or damage to or`
  line `destruction of property or disrupts or knowing that it is likely to cause damage or disruption of supplies or`
  line `services essential to the life of the community or adversely affect the critical information infrastructure`
  line `specified under section 70; or`
  line
  line `(B) knowingly or intentionally penetrates or accesses a computer resource without authorisation or`
  line `exceeding authorised access, and by means of such conduct obtains access to information, data or`
  line `computer data base that is restricted for reasons of the security of the State or foreign relations; or any`
  line `restricted information, data or computer data base, with reasons to believe that such information, data`
  line `or computer data base so obtained may be used to cause or likely to cause injury to the interests of the`
  line `sovereignty and integrity of India, the security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States,`
  line `public order, decency or morality, or in relation to contempt of court, defamation or incitement to an`
  line `offence, or to the advantage of any foreign nation, group of individuals or otherwise,`
  line
  line `commits the offence of cyber terrorism.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever commits or conspires to commit cyber terrorism shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to imprisonment for life`
obj_root_law_sections_66_f_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (13092)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 83
  title `Punishment for publishing or transmitting obscene material in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13092&sectionno=67&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `publishes or transmits or causes to be published or transmitted in the electronic form, any material which`
  line `is lascivious or appeals to the prurient interest or if its effect is such as to tend to deprave and corrupt`
  line `persons who are likely, having regard to all relevant circumstances, to read, see or hear the matter`
  line `contained or embodied in it, shall be punished on first conviction with imprisonment of either description`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years and with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees and in the`
  line `event of second or subsequent conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may`
  line `extend to five years and also with fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67_a:
  sectionId (13093)
  sectionNo 67A
  orderNo 84
  title `Punishment for publishing or transmitting of material containing sexually explicit act, etc., in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13093&sectionno=67A&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content:
  string
  line `Whoever publishes or transmits or causes to be published or transmitted in the`
  line `electronic form any material which contains sexually explicit act or conduct shall be punished on first`
  line `conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to five years and with`
  line `fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees and in the event of second or subsequent conviction with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years and also with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67_b:
  sectionId (13094)
  sectionNo 67B
  orderNo 85
  title `Punishment for publishing or transmitting of material depicting children in sexually explicit act, etc., in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13094&sectionno=67B&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_67_b_content:
  string
  line Whoever,--
  line
  line `(a) publishes or transmits or causes to be published or transmitted material in any electronic form`
  line `which depicts children engaged in sexually explicit act or conduct; or`
  line
  line `(b) creates text or digital images, collects, seeks, browses, downloads, advertises, promotes,`
  line `exchanges or distributes material in any electronic form depicting children in obscene or indecent or`
  line `sexually explicit manner; or`
  line
  line `(c) cultivates, entices or induces children to online relationship with one or more children for and`
  line `on sexually explicit act or in a manner that may offend a reasonable adult on the computer resource; or`
  line
  line `(d) facilitates abusing children online, or`
  line
  line `(e) records in any electronic form own abuse or that of others pertaining to sexually explicit act`
  line `with children,`
  line
  line `shall be punished on first conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to five years and with fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees and in the event of second or subsequent`
  line `conviction with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to seven years and also`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that provisions of section 67, section 67A and this section does not extend to any book,`
  line `pamphlet, paper, writing, drawing, painting representation or figure in electronic form--`
  line
  line `(i) the publication of which is proved to be justified as being for the public good on the ground`
  line `that such book, pamphlet, paper, writing, drawing, painting representation or figure is the interest`
  line `of science, literature, art or learning or other objects of general concern; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which is kept or used for bona fide heritage or religious purposes.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of this section, "children" means a person who has not completed the`
  line `age of 18 years.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67_c:
  sectionId (13095)
  sectionNo 67C
  orderNo 86
  title `Preservation and retention of information by intermediaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13095&sectionno=67C&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_67_c_content:
  string
  line `67C. Preservation and retention of information by intermediaries.–(1) Intermediary shall`
  line `preserve and retain such information as may be specified for such duration and in such manner and format`
  line `as the Central Government may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) any intermediary who intentionally or knowingly contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be ^1[liable to penalty which may extend to twenty-five lakh rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (13096)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power of Controller to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 33, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13096&sectionno=68&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller may, by order, direct a Certifying`
  line `Authority or any employee of such Authority to take such measures or cease carrying on such activities as`
  line `specified in the order if those are necessary to ensure compliance with the provisions of this Act, rules or`
  line `any regulations made thereunder.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) Any person who intentionally or knowingly fails to comply with any order under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable on conviction to imprisonment for a term not exceeding`
  line `two years or a fine not exceeding one lakh rupees or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (13097)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power to issue directions for interception or monitoring or decryption of any information through any computer resource.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for section 69 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13097&sectionno=69&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[69. Power to issue directions for interception or monitoring or decryption of any information`
  line `through any computer resource.--(1) Where the Central Government or a State Government or any of`
  line `its officers specially authorised by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `in this behalf may, if satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, in the interest of the sovereignty`
  line `or integrity of India, defence of India, security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States or public`
  line `order or for preventing incitement to the commission of any cognizable offence relating to above or for`
  line `investigation of any offence, it may subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), for reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing, by order, direct any agency of the appropriate Government to intercept, monitor or decrypt or`
  line `cause to be intercepted or monitored or decrypted any information generated, transmitted, received or`
  line `stored in any computer resource.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure and safeguards subject to which such interception or monitoring or decryption may`
  line `be carried out, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The subscriber or intermediary or any person in-charge of the computer resource shall, when called`
  line `upon by any agency referred to in sub-section (1), extend all facilities and technical assistance to--`
  line
  line `(a) provide access to or secure access to the computer resource generating, transmitting, receiving`
  line `or storing such information; or`
  line
  line `(b) intercept, monitor, or decrypt the information, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(c) provide information stored in computer resource.`
  line
  line `(4) The subscriber or intermediary or any person who fails to assist the agency referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_a:
  sectionId (13098)
  sectionNo 69A
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to issue directions for blocking for public access of any information through any computer resource.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13098&sectionno=69A&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_69_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government or any of its officers specially authorised by it in`
  line `this behalf is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, in the interest of sovereignty and integrity`
  line `of India, defence of India, security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States or public order or for`
  line `preventing incitement to the commission of any cognizable offence relating to above, it may subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), for reasons to be recorded in writing, by order, direct any agency of the`
  line `Government or intermediary to block for access by the public or cause to be blocked for access by the`
  line `public any information generated, transmitted, received, stored or hosted in any computer resource.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure and safeguards subject to which such blocking for access by the public may be`
  line `carried out, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The intermediary who fails to comply with the direction issued under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `punished with an imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69_b:
  sectionId (13099)
  sectionNo 69B
  orderNo 90
  title `Power to authorise to monitor and collect traffic data or information through any computer resource for cyber security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for "three years and shall also be liable to fine" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13099&sectionno=69B&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_69_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[69B. Power to authorise to monitor and collect traffic data or information through any`
  line `computer resource for cyber security.--(1) The Central Government may, to enhance cyber security and`
  line `for identification, analysis and prevention of intrusion or spread of computer contaminant in the country,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise any agency of the Government to monitor and collect`
  line `traffic data or information generated, transmitted, received or stored in any computer resource.`
  line
  line `(2) The intermediary or any person in-charge or the computer resource shall, when called upon by the`
  line `agency which has been authorised under sub-section (1), provide technical assistance and extend all`
  line `facilities to such agency to enable online access or to secure and provide online access to the computer`
  line `resource generating, transmitting, receiving or storing such traffic data or information.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure and safeguards for monitoring and collecting traffic data or information, shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any intermediary who intentionally or knowingly contravenes the provisions of sub-section (2)`
  line `shall be punished with an imprisonment for a term which any extend to ^2[one year or shall be liable to fine`
  line `which may extend to one crore rupees, or with both].`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "computer contaminant" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 43;`
  line
  line `(ii) "traffic data" means any data identifying or purporting to identify any person, computer`
  line `system or computer network or location to or from which the communication is or may be`
  line `transmitted and includes communications origin, destination, route, time, data, size, duration or`
  line `type of underlying service and any other information.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (13100)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 91
  title `Protected system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13100&sectionno=70&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare any computer resource which directly or indirectly affects the facility of Critical Information`
  line `Infrastructure, to be a protected system.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "Critical Information Infrastructure" means the`
  line `computer resource, the incapacitation or destruction of which, shall have debilitating impact on national`
  line `security, economy, public health or safety.]`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, by order in writing, authorise the persons who are authorised to`
  line `access protected systems notified under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who secures access or attempts to secure access to a protected system in contravention`
  line `of the provisions of this section shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(4) The Central Government shall prescribe the information security practices and procedures for`
  line `such protected system.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 35, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
obj_root_law_sections_70_a:
  sectionId (13101)
  sectionNo 70A
  orderNo 92
  title `National nodal agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13101&sectionno=70A&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_70_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[70A. National nodal agency.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, designate any organisation of the Government as the national nodal agency in respect of`
  line `Critical Information Infrastructure Protection`
  line
  line `(2) The national nodal agency designated under sub-section (1) shall be responsible for all measures`
  line `including Research and Development relating to protection of Critical Information Infrastructure.`
  line
  line `(3) The manner of performing functions and duties of the agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70_b:
  sectionId (13102)
  sectionNo 70B
  orderNo 93
  title `Indian Computer Emergency Response Team to serve as national agency for incident response.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for "one lakh" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13102&sectionno=70B&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_70_b_content:
  string
  line `^1]70B. Indian Computer Emergency Response Team to serve as national agency for incident`
  line `response.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint an agency of`
  line `the Government to be called the Indian Computer Emergency Response Team.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall provide the agency referred to in sub-section (1) with a Director`
  line `General and such other officers and employees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances and terms and conditions of the Director-General and other officers and`
  line `employees shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Indian Computer Emergency Response Team shall serve as the national agency for`
  line `performing the following functions in the area of cyber security,–-`
  line
  line `(a) collection, analysis and dissemination of information on cyber incidents;`
  line
  line `(b) forecast and alerts of cyber security incidents;`
  line
  line `(c) emergency measures for handling cyber security incidents;`
  line
  line `(d) coordination of cyber incidents response activities;`
  line
  line `(e) issue guidelines, advisories, vulnerability notes and white papers relating to information`
  line `security practices, procedures, preventation, response and reporting of cyber incidents;`
  line
  line `(f) such other functions relating to cyber security as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The manner of performing functions and duties of the agency referred to in sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) For carrying out the provisions of sub-section (4), the agency referred to in sub-section (1) may`
  line `call for information and give direction to the service providers, intermediaries, data centres, body`
  line `corporate and any other person.`
  line
  line `(7) Any service provider, intermediaries, data centres, body corporate or person who fails to provide`
  line `the information called for or comply with the direction under sub-section (6), shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine which may extend to ^1[one crore]`
  line `rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(8) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this section, except on a complaint made by`
  line `an officer authorised in this behalf by the agency referred to in sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (13103)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 94
  title `Penalty for misrepresentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 2, for "Digital Signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13103&sectionno=71&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes any misrepresentation to, or suppresses any`
  line `material fact from the Controller or the Certifying Authority for obtaining any licence or ^1`
  line [electronic
  line `signature Certificate], as the case may be, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (13104)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 95
  title `Penalty for Breach of confidentiality and privacy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain world (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13104&sectionno=72&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, if any person who, in pursuance of any of the powers conferred`
  line `under this Act, rules or regulations made thereunder, has secured access to any electronic record, book,`
  line `register, correspondence, information, document or other material without the consent of the person`
  line `concerned discloses such electronic record, book, register, correspondence, information, document or`
  line `other material to any other person shall be ^1[liable to penalty which may extend to five lakh rupees[.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_a:
  sectionId (13105)
  sectionNo 72A
  orderNo 96
  title `Punishment for disclosure of information in breach of lawful contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13105&sectionno=72A&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_72_a_content:
  string
  line ^1[72A.
  line `^2[Penalty] for disclosure of information in breach of lawful contract.---Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, any person including an intermediary`
  line `who, while providing services under the terms of lawful contract, has secured access to any material containing personal information about another person, with the intent to cause or knowing that he is likely`
  line `to cause wrongful loss or wrongful gain discloses, without the consent of the person concerned, or in`
  line `breach of a lawful contract, such material to any other person, shall be ^3[liable to penalty which may`
  line `extend to twenty-five lakh rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_72_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 37, (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for "Punishment" (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for certain word (w.e.f. 30-11-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (13106)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 97
  title `Penalty for publishing electronic signature Certificate false in certain particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 38, for section 77 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13106&sectionno=73&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `73. Penalty for publishing ^1[electronic signature] Certificate false in certain particulars.--(1) No`
  line `person shall publish a ^1[electronic signature] Certificate or otherwise make it available to any other person`
  line `with the knowledge that--`
  line
  line `(a) the Certifying Authority listed in the certificate has not issued it; or`
  line
  line `(b) the subscriber listed in the certificate has not accepted it; or`
  line
  line `(c) the certificate has been revoked or suspended,`
  line
  line `unless such publication is for the purpose of verifying a ^1[electronic signature] created prior to such`
  line `suspension or revocation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (13107)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 98
  title `Publication for fraudulent purpose.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 38, for section 77 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13107&sectionno=74&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly creates, publishes or otherwise makes`
  line `available a ^1`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate for any fraudulent or unlawful purpose shall be punished`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (13108)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 99
  title `Act to apply for offence or contravention committed outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13108&sectionno=75&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), the provisions of this Act shall apply also to any offence or contravention`
  line `committed outside India by any person irrespective of his nationality.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), this Act shall apply to an offence or contravention committed`
  line `outside India by any person if the act or conduct constituting the offence or contravention involves a`
  line `computer, computer system or computer network located in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (13109)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 100
  title Confiscation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13109&sectionno=76&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Any computer, computer system, floppies, compact disks, tape drives or any other`
  line `accessories related thereto, in respect of which any provision of this Act, rules, orders or regulations made`
  line `thereunder has been or is being contravened, shall be liable to confiscation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is established to the satisfaction of the court adjudicating the confiscation that`
  line `the person in whose possession, power or control of any such computer, computer system, floppies,`
  line `compact disks, tape drives or any other accessories relating thereto is found is not responsible for the`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act, rules, orders or regulations made thereunder, the court may,`
  line `instead of making an order for confiscation of such computer, computer system, floppies, compact disks,`
  line `tape drives or any other accessories related thereto, make such other order authorised by this Act against`
  line `the person contravening of the provisions of this Act, rules, orders or regulations made thereunder as it`
  line `may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (13110)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 101
  title `Compensation, penalties or confiscation not to interfere with other punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 38, for section 77 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13110&sectionno=77&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[77. Compensation, penalties or confiscation not to interfere with other punishment.--No`
  line `compensation awarded, penalty imposed or confiscation made under this Act shall prevent the award of`
  line `compensation or imposition of any other penalty or punishment under any other law for the time being in`
  line force.]
obj_root_law_sections_77_a:
  sectionId (13111)
  sectionNo 77A
  orderNo 102
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 38, for section 77 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13111&sectionno=77A&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[77A. Compounding of offences.--A court of competent jurisdiction may compound offences, other`
  line `than offences for which the punishment for life or imprisonment for a term exceeding three years has`
  line `been provided, under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court shall not compound such offence where the accused is, by reason of his`
  line `previous conviction, liable to either enhanced punishment or to a punishment of a different kind:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the court shall not compound any offence where such offence affects the socio`
  line `economic conditions of the country or has been committed against a child below the age of 18 years or a`
  line woman.
  line
  line `(2) The person accused of an offence under this Act may file an application for compounding in the`
  line `court in which offence is pending for trial and the provisions of sections 265B and 265C of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_77_b:
  sectionId (13112)
  sectionNo 77B
  orderNo 103
  title `Offences with three years imprisonment to be bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 38, for section 77 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13112&sectionno=77B&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_77_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[77B. Offences with three years imprisonment to be bailable.--Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the offence punishable with imprisonment of three`
  line `years and above shall be cognizable and the offence punishable with imprisonment of three years shall be`
  line bailable.
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (13113)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power to investigate offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 39, for "Deputy Superintendent of Police" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13113&sectionno=78&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a police officer not below the rank of ^1`
  line `[Inspector] shall investigate any`
  line `offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (13114)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 105
  title `Exemption from liability of intermediary in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by, s. 40, ibid., for Chapter XII (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13114&sectionno=79&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `^1[79. Exemption from liability of intermediary in certain cases.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force but subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3),`
  line `an intermediary shall not be liable for any third party information, data, or communication link made`
  line `available or hosted by him.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply if--`
  line
  line `(a) the function of the intermediary is limited to providing access to a communication system over`
  line `which information made available by third parties is transmitted or temporarily stored or hosted; or`
  line
  line `(b) the intermediary does not--`
  line
  line `(i) initiate the transmission,`
  line
  line `(ii) select the receiver of the transmission, and`
  line
  line `(iii) select or modify the information contained in the transmission;`
  line
  line `(c) the intermediary observes due diligence while discharging his duties under this Act and also`
  line `observes such other guidelines as the Central Government may prescribe in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply if--`
  line
  line `(a) the intermediary has conspired or abetted or aided or induced, whether by threats or promise or`
  line `otherwise in the commission of the unlawful act;`
  line
  line `(b) upon receiving actual knowledge, or on being notified by the appropriate Government or its`
  line `agency that any information, data or communication link residing in or connected to a computer`
  line `resource controlled by the intermediary is being used to commit the unlawful act, the intermediary`
  line `fails to expeditiously remove or disable access to that material on that resource without vitiating the`
  line `evidence in any manner.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section, the expression "third party information" means any`
  line `information dealt with by an intermediary in his capacity as an intermediary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_79_a:
  sectionId (13115)
  sectionNo 79A
  orderNo 106
  title `Central Government to notify Examiner of Electronic Evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by, s. 40, ibid., for Chapter XII (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13115&sectionno=79A&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_79_a_content:
  string
  line `[79A. Central Government to notify Examiner of Electronic Evidence.--The Central Government`
  line `may, for the purposes of providing expert opinion on electronic form evidence before any court or other`
  line `authority specify, by notification in the Official Gazette, any Department, body or agency of the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government as an Examiner of Electronic Evidence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section, "electronic form evidence" means any information of`
  line `probative value that is either stored or transmitted in electronic form and includes computer evidence,`
  line `digital audio, digital video, cell phones, digital fax machines.]`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (13116)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 107
  title `Power of police officer and other officers to enter, search, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 41, for "Deputy Superintendent of Police" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13116&sectionno=80&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any police officer, not below the rank of a`
  line ^1
  line `[Inspector], or any other officer of the Central Government or a State Government authorised by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf may enter any public place and search and arrest without warrant any`
  line `person found therein who is reasonably suspected of having committed or of committing or of being`
  line `about to commit any offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "public place" includes any public`
  line `conveyance, any hotel, any shop or any other place intended for use by, or accessible to the public.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person is arrested under sub-section (1) by an officer other than a police officer, such`
  line `officer shall, without unnecessary delay, take or send the person arrested before a magistrate having`
  line `jurisdiction in the case or before the officer-in-charge of a police station.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall, subject to the provisions`
  line `of this section, apply, so far as may be, in relation to any entry, search or arrest, made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (13117)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 108
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes `1Ins. by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13117&sectionno=81&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that nothing contained in this Act shall restrict any person from exercising any right`
  line `conferred under the Copyright Act, 1957 (14 of 1957) or the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of 1970).]`
obj_root_law_sections_81_a:
  sectionId (13118)
  sectionNo 81A
  orderNo 109
  title `Application of the Act to electronic cheque and truncated cheque.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 55 of 2002, s. 13 (w.e.f. 26-2-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13118&sectionno=81A&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_81_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[81A. Application of the Act to electronic cheque and truncated cheque.--(1) The provisions of`
  line `this Act, for the time being in force, shall apply to, or in relation to, electronic cheques and the truncated`
  line `cheques subject to such modifications and amendments as may be necessary for carrying out the purposes`
  line `of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881) by the Central Government, in consultation with the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India, by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not`
  line `be made, the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this Act, the expressions "electronic cheque" and "truncated cheque"`
  line `shall have the same meaning as assigned to them in section 6 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26`
  line `of 1881).]`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (13119)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 110
  title `Controller, Deputy Controller and Assistant Controller to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by 7 of 2017, s. 169, for section 82 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13119&sectionno=82&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[82. Controller, Deputy Controller and Assistant Controller to be public servants.-- The`
  line `Controller, the Deputy Controller and the Assistant Controllers shall be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (13120)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13120&sectionno=83&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give directions to any State Government`
  line `as to the carrying into execution in the State of any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule, regulation`
  line `or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (13121)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 112
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13121&sectionno=84&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Central Government, the State Government, the Controller or any person acting on behalf of`
  line `him, ^1[]and adjudicating officer] for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or any rule, regulation or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 169, ibid., for "the Chairperson Members, adjudicating officers and the staff of the Cyber Appellate Tribunal"`
  line `(w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
obj_root_law_sections_84_a:
  sectionId (13122)
  sectionNo 84A
  orderNo 113
  title `Modes or methods for encryption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by 10 of 2009, s. 45 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13122&sectionno=84A&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_84_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[84A. Modes or methods for encryption.--The Central Government may, for secure use of the`
  line `electronic medium and for promotion of e-governance and e-commerce, prescribe the modes or methods`
  line `for encryption.]`
obj_root_law_sections_84_b:
  sectionId (13123)
  sectionNo 84B
  orderNo 114
  title `Punishment for abetment of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by 10 of 2009, s. 45 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13123&sectionno=84B&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_84_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[84B. Punishment for abetment of offences.--Whoever abets any offence shall, if the act abetted is`
  line `committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Act for the`
  line `punishment of such abetment, be punished with the punishment provided for the offence under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An act or offence is said to be committed in consequence of abetment, when it is`
  line `committed in consequence of the instigation, or in pursuance of the conspiracy, or with the aid which`
  line `constitutes the abetment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_84_c:
  sectionId (13124)
  sectionNo 84C
  orderNo 115
  title `Punishment for attempt to commit offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by 10 of 2009, s. 45 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13124&sectionno=84C&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_84_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[84C. Punishment for attempt to commit offences.--Whoever attempts to commit an offence`
  line `punishable by this Act or causes such an offence to be committed, and in such an attempt does any act`
  line `towards the commission of the offence, shall, where no express provision is made for the punishment of`
  line `such attempt, be punished with imprisonment of any description provided for the offence, for a term`
  line `which may extend to one-half of the longest term of imprisonment provided for that offence, or with such`
  line `fine as is provided for the offence, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (13125)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 116
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13125&sectionno=85&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person committing a contravention of any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder is a company, every person who, at the time`
  line `the contravention was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct`
  line `of business of the company as well as the company, shall be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable`
  line `to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to punishment if`
  line `he proves that the contravention took place without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to`
  line `prevent such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the contravention has taken place with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company,`
  line `such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of the contravention`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) 'company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (13126)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 117
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13126&sectionno=86&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (13127)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 118
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13127&sectionno=87&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette and in the Electronic Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) the conditions for considering reliability of electronic signature or electronic authentication`
  line `technique under sub-section (2) of section 3A;`
  line
  line `(aa) the procedure for ascertaining electronic signature or authentication under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3A;`
  line
  line `(ab) the manner in which any information or matter may be authenticated by means of electronic`
  line `signature under section 5;]`
  line
  line `(b) the electronic form in which filing, issue, grant or payment shall be effected under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner and format in which electronic records shall be filed, or issued and the method of`
  line `payment under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ca) the manner in which the authorised service provider may collect, retain and appropriate`
  line `service charges under sub-section (2) of section 6A;]`
  line
  line `(d) the matters relating to the type of ^3`
  line `[electronic signature], manner and format in which it may be`
  line `affixed under section 10;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(e) the manner of storing and affixing electronic signature creation data under section 15;`
  line
  line `(ea) the security procedures and practices under section 16;]`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications, experience and terms and conditions of service of Controller, Deputy`
  line `Controllers ^5`
  line `[, Assistant Controllers, other officers and employees] under section 17;`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) the requirements which an applicant must fulfil under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(i) the period of validity of licence granted under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(j) the form in which an application for licence may be made under sub-section (1) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(k) the amount of fees payable under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(l) such other documents which shall accompany an application for licence under clause (d) of subsection (2) of section 22;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and the fee for renewal of a licence and the fee payable thereof under section 23;`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(ma) the form of application and fee for issue of Electronic Signature Certificate under`
  line `section 35;]`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which application for issue of a ^3`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate may be made`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(o) the fee to be paid to the Certifying Authority for issue of a ^3`
  line `[electronic signature] Certificate`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 35;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(oa) the duties of subscribers under section 40A;`
  line
  line `(ob) the reasonable security practices and procedures and sensitive personal data or information`
  line `under section 43A;]`
  line
  line `(p) the manner in which the adjudicating officer shall hold inquiry under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 46;
  line
  line `(q) the qualification and experience which the adjudicating officer shall possess under sub-section`
  line `(3) of section 46;`
  line
  line ^8
  line `* * * *`
  line
  line `(u) the form in which appeal may be filed and the fee thereof under sub-section (3) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(v) any other power of a civil court required to be prescribed under clause (g) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 58; and`
  line
  line ^9
  line `[(w) the powers and functions of the Chairperson of the ^10`
  line `[Appellate Tribunal] under`
  line `section 52A;`
  line
  line `(x) the information, duration, manner and form of such information to be retained and preserved`
  line `under section 67C;`
  line
  line `(y) the procedures and safeguards for interception, monitoring or decryption under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 69;`
  line
  line `(z) the procedures and safeguards for blocking for access by the public under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 69 A;`
  line
  line `(za) the procedure and safeguards for monitoring and collecting traffic data or information under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 69B;`
  line
  line `(zb) the information security practices and procedures for protected system under section 70;`
  line
  line `(zc) manner of performing functions and duties of the agency under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 70A;`
  line
  line `(zd) the officers and employees under sub-section (2) of section 70B;`
  line
  line `(ze) salaries and allowances and terms and conditions of service of the Director General and other`
  line `officers and employees under sub-section (3) of section 70B;`
  line
  line `(zf) the manner in which the functions and duties of agency shall be performed under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 70B;`
  line
  line `(zg) the guidelines to be observed by the intermediaries under sub-section (2) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(zh) the modes or methods for encryption under section 84A.]`
  line
  line `(3)`
  line ^11
  line `[Every notification made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 70A and`
  line `every rule made by it] shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in ^12`
  line `*** the rule or both`
  line `Houses agree that ^12`
  line `*** the rule should not be made, ^12`
  line `*** the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that notification or`
  line rule.
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 46 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "digital signature" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for "and Assistant Controllers" (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (g) omitted by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `8. Clauses (r), (s) and (t) omitted by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 46, for clause (w) (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 169, for "Cyber Appellate Tribunal"(w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 10 of 2009, s. 46, for certain words, brackets, letter and figures (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  line
  line `12. The words "the notification or" omitted by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (13128)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 119
  title `Constitution of Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13128&sectionno=88&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, constitute a Committee called the Cyber Regulations Advisory`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(2) The Cyber Regulations Advisory Committee shall consist of a Chairperson and such number of`
  line `other official and non-official members representing the interests principally affected or having special`
  line `knowledge of the subject-matter as the Central Government may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Cyber Regulations Advisory Committee shall advise--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government either generally as regards any rules or for any other purpose`
  line `connected with this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the Controller in framing the regulations under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be paid to the non-official members of such Committee such travelling and other`
  line `allowances as the Central Government may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (13129)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 120
  title `Power of Controller to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by notification No. S.O. 1015(E), for "(m)" (w.e.f. 19-9-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13129&sectionno=89&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller may, after consultation with the`
  line `Cyber Regulations Advisory Committee and with the previous approval of the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the particulars relating to maintenance of data base containing the disclosure record of every`
  line `Certifying Authority under clause ^1[(n)] of section 18;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions and restrictions subject to which the Controller may recognise any foreign`
  line `Certifying Authority under sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions subject to which a licence may be granted under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) other standards to be observed by a Certifying Authority under clause (d) of section 30;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which the Certifying Authority shall disclose the matters specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(f) the particulars of statement which shall accompany an application under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 35.`
  line
  line `(g) the manner by which the subscriber shall communicate the compromise of private key to the`
  line `Certifying Authority under sub-section (2) of section 42.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (13130)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 121
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (c) omitted by Act 10 of 2009, s. 47 (w.e.f. 27-10-2009).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077&sectionId=13130&sectionno=90&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_45_76_00001_200021_1517807324077
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the electronic form in which filing, issue, grant, receipt or payment shall be effected under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) for matters specified in sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
